Description: Fragment of pottery amphora (?), central part of base; red dipinto in centre; inside surface completely lost. Hard, orange clay, Munsell 5YR 6/6 (reddish yellow); little mica.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (G), chamber 29
Curator's comments: Findspot number '29' pencilled on the item
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 351)
Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (pl. xxxii, left, 2nd from top.)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.128, p.129, p.211, p.226, pl.68)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
